nToomey 21 139 389 12 51 111.17\nBenson 30 142 374 13 75 110-22\nChaconas 78 135 357 42 168 108-50\nTalbert 36 144 368 10 75 106- 8\nHurd 138 327 4 10 106- 4\nAiken 19 128 331 11 35 106-\nCoCUjM 43 140 854 14 86 105-29\nB. Bromley.. 69 128 352 29 133 105- 2\nBailey 50 150 382 21 84 103-20\nNATIONALS\nSweeney 78 158 390 35 186 109-40\nMcKay 75 140 396 36 151 108-34\nBa lm er 73 143 374 29 156 107-39\nWescott 9 132 314 5 16 104- 2\nC. Lavender.. 39 131 336 17 65 103-10\nB. Lavender .53 151 343 22 85 102- 1\nBrown 64 121 309 20 88 97-15\nNOMADS\nStephenson 33 132 346 16 71 109- 1\nOberman 41 146 378 25 89 108-38\nSchroen 75 146 368 33 158 106- 5\nPestell 66 148 388 25 141 105-29\nCroghan 69 141 347 33 126 104-48\nSteer 50 128 346 14 90 103-33\nReckewag 65 128 341 24 115 100- 7\nHUGH REILLY CO.\nGreen 44 141 837 21 68 101-\nGray 81 141 857 27 128 99-46\nWinters 80 135 386 24 110 97-35\nWeaver 77 129 338 19 111 97- 9\nBrels 71 125 329 21 95 96-23\nButler 9 114 300 2 14 96- 8\nSawyer 16 107 297 8 17 94-10\nSUITS MID TOPCOATS\nMade to Order\non the premises <DOO\nJICI BERNSTEIN, Inc.\niU F ST. N. W.\nFnn Dress and Tuxedo Suite to Hiee\nFRIDAY, APRIL 22, 1927\nBy Gene Knott\nU. S. GOLFERS\nSEEK TITLE\nJess W. Sfweetser will not defend\nhis title as amateur golf champion\nof Great Britain, but America will\nnot go unrepresented in the tourna\nment that is to decide his successor.\nSeven .American players already\nhave signified their intention to play\nin the British event, which is to be\nheld this year at Hoylake during the\nweek of May 23.\nThe seven are \"Walter Richard,\nJoshua Crane. Frank C. Newton,\nSilas M. Newton, William C. Fownea,\njr\u201e R. O. Morrison and William\nBrower. Most of the fytt six named\nalready ha\"ve sailed, while Ute last\nnamed is a sftident at Cambridge.\nComfort Rules\nIn Stance for\nJigger\nBy Charles (Chick) Evans, Jr.\nMy grip on this club is usually\nabout the middle of the leather, for\non all iron shots it seems the best\nplace to get that much wanted\nbalance of '\u2018feel.\"\nI know very good goiferg who\ngrip the club with the left hand\nat the very end. but as a general\nrule if one is not getting the head\nheavy, feeling it is-better to drop\nthe hands down on the leather even\nso far as the whipping at the end\nof the leather.\nRudy Knepper is successful\nexponent of this method. Os\ncourse, I am absolutely sure\nthere is but one way to grip\niron clubs, and that is in the\nfingers\u2014never in the palms.\nThe only way to get the truly\nsensitive finger-grip is with the\nthumbs on the shaft.\nDo not put them exactly straight\ndown it, however, but the. thumbs\nshould be so placed to one side that\na narrow intersection of them rests\nupon the shafts. The grip should\npireefion _ j\nT\nf\nCROUCH A_ a\nI\u2014 I BIT J\nADDJRESr SgH\nTbq L\u00b12zJ'\nI x- s ..I\nbe firm, but not tight and it should\nnot change again at any time of\nthe stroke.\nComfort should rule your\nstance. I believe thafr you\ncan get a freer stroke If\nyour left foot is a little behind\nyour right. I would not over\ndo this, however, nor would I\nget it too nearly square, but\nwould Just keep stepping around\nuntil your individual require\nment is met. for bear in mind,\nwe are all different.\nYour fteet should not be as far\napart in this shot as in some of\nthe longer clubs, but one should\nhave a firm feeling of solidity.\nBoth heels should be on the ground\neven though the weight rests 'on\nthe balls of the feet.\n(Copyright. John F. Dllle Co.)\nFnrnlohed apartments <\u2014onfnrniohed\napartment*. Select the one you want\nte rent from the Rental ColumiM of The\nXlnuM Axui BmtolA CIamMUmI A4tw\nINDIANSRUN\nIN MEET\nf\nCHICAGO, April 22.\u2014The crunch\nof gravel under the speeding feet of\nwhite-trunked athletes will echo over\nthe campus of two prominent uni\nversities tomorrow, signalizing the\nofficial opening of the 1927 inter\ncollegiate outdoor track and field\nseason in the Middle West.\nThe opening events are the\nKansas and Ohio State relay\ngames, the former at Lawrence.\nKans., and the latter at Colum\nbus. More than 2,000 athletes,\nrepresenting 300 colleges and\nuniversities throughout the land,\nwill take part in the two events.\nThe feature attraction of the\nKansas games will be the appear\nance of the famous Tarahumara\nIndian runners from Chihuahua.\nMexico. They will run a mere 66\nmiles from Kansas City to Law\nrence, starting early tomorrow.\nThree women of the same tribe will\nrun from Topeka, Kans., to Law\nrence, a distance of 27 miles.\nCapt. Charles McGinnis of the.\nUniversity of Wisconsin, and\nCapt. Anton Burg ot Chicago,\nare two of the Big Ten\u2019s most\nnoted individual stars who will\nshow their wares at the \u2019Ohio\nState games. They will compete\nin the running broad Jump.\nSpence of the City College of De\ntroit, National Collegiate A. A.\nchampion In low hurdles: McAtee\nof Michigan State, and Glaser of\nMarquette\u2014the latter two pole\nvaulters\u2014will also be seen at Ohio\nState.\nHerb Pennock Will Be\nLost to Yankee Team\nNEW YORK, April 21. The\ntroubles of Miller Huggins, manager\nof the Yankees, are coming in\nbunches. Herb Pennock, southpaw,\nwho hurt his foot in batting prac\ntice. will not be available for serv\nice in this series with the Athletics,\nnor ie he likely to be in shape for\nthe series with the Washington\nSenators, starting Sunday.\nHerb had an X-ray taken of the\ninjury, which has been very pain\nful. The X-ray showed no broken\nbone nor any fractuee. Herb is on\ncrutches.\nPriest Devises An\nAll-Shot Golf\nClub\nCHICAGO. April 22.\u2014The\nKev. Alphonse Gavin, a Catholic\npriest, tired of lugging a bag\nfull of golf clubs around the\ngolf course he laid out in his\ndesert parish at Goldfield, Nev.,\n\u2022\u2019evised a club to serve as driver,\nbrassie, midiron, mashie and\nputter.\nThe club has a face adjust\nable on a steel cog to six\npositions.\nOur Service Station\nIs Open\nDaily and Sunday\nfrom 8 A.M. to 12 P.M.\nLeave your car at night and\nit will be washed and ready at\n8 a. m. next morning.\nJos.Mc\u00dfeynolds, inc.\nSERVICE STATION\nKansas Ave. \u00bb4 Upshur St\nColumbia 3052\n\nGOLF CLUBS\nof the Better Kind\nup\nSPORT MART\n\u202214 F 8t. lm r BT I4M N. T. Ave.\n\u2713T\u2019X Diamnfc.Watches,Jewelry\nO ROSSLYN\nA LOAN CO.\nW ROSSLYN. VA.\nEnd Key Rrtdce\u2014Rosalyn Car to Door\nDIAMOND CABS\nPOTOMAC\n6200\nLOWEST RATES\nIN WASHINGTON\ntarn ft a\n.TAIUOmNO CO.\nFive Leading Batters\nOs Major Leagued\n-AMERICAN LEAGUE\nCotllnn, N. T 6 4 .506\nHeilraann. D0t..... I It 3 9 Ma\nJndsa. Waah t N t is .4tt\nGehrig, N. T 14 87 88 17 .449\nCombe. N. T M 48 19 .453\nLeader a year ago today' Flauetead,\nBoeton, .lit.\nNATIONAL LEAGUE\nG AB R It Pet.\nSand, Phlla. 1 17 9 u .519\nTyaon. N. Y 8 M 12 AW\nHornsby, N. Y.... 9 34 U 15 .441\nLtftdstrom, N. T... 9 44 6 17 .435\nHafey, St. Loula.. 7 M 4 11 .4231\nLeader a year ago today, HarMby, BL.\nLouie, .438.\ni Teeterday\u2019a Heme Saw f\nNATIONAL LEAGUE\nNo. Total\nWilliams, Phillies. 1\nWrightaone, Phi11ie5..,..,.... 1 3\nLindstrom, Giants.l\nKremer, Pirates 1,1\nAMERICAN LIAGUE,\nGehrig, Yankees. .............I t 1\nTobin. Red Sox2\nLaaaeri, Yankees 1\nThe Leaders\nNATIONAL LEAGUE\nWilllame (4). Wilson (te). -Hornsby\nHarper (2), Webb (J2>, Wright\nalone 2). 1\nAMERICAN LEAGIUE\nGehrig (3), Simmons (3),f Tebin (3).\nand Ruth L f\nLeague Totals\nNational, 28.\nAmerican, it.\nSPORTS CARNIVAC\nThree hundred and fifty con\ntestants took part in the annual\nindoor athletic carnival at Purdue\nUniversity, the events\neverything from bicycle races to\nbasketball games.\nJOCKEY IN COMEBACK\nWinnie O\u2019Connor, America\u2019s fa\nmous jockey who holds the record\nfor winners with 2,500 mounts, is\nplanning to stage a come-back at\nthe age. of 44.\nI\nDAVID HEBBON, Pre*,\nSTOKE HOURS:\nDaily, 8 A. M. to 9 P. M. Saturday Until 11:30 P. M.\nSunday; Till 1 P. M.\nMOBILOIL 5\nOne-gallon can New \\Y*\nStandard me- \\^y g 